<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>However, we must be careful not to ascribe properties to a machine that the particular machine doesn't have.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>We humans can easily fool ourselves when there is something we want to believe.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>If designers and programmers think about the apparent mental qualities that their programs will have, they'll create programs that are easier and pleasanter -- more humane -- to deal with.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>It is easiest to uderstand the ascription of thoughts to machines in circumstances when we also understand the machine in physical terms.</a>
<a name="4">[4]</a> <a href="#4" id=4>The mental qualities of present machines are not the same as ours.</a>
